<div class="panel-heading">
	<h1 class="panel-title light gray">Example 1</h1>
</div>
<div class="panel-body">
	<p class="instruction bold"><strong>Step 1:</strong> Read the following sentence carefully.</p>
	<p class="question_sentence">
		<span id="arg1">Bill Clinton</span> , former <span id="arg2">US</span> President , spoke at a conference on national debt last week .
	</p>
	
	<p class="instruction bold"><strong>Step 2:</strong> Based on what you read, complete the following sentence using the options below. (For this question, &ldquo;lived in&rdquo; and &ldquo;has nationality&rdquo; are the correct answers.) <!-- Button trigger modal -->
<button class="btn btn-primary btn-xs" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#myModal">
  Read Explanation
</button></p>
	<p class="blank_sentence"><span id="arg1"> Bill Clinton </span> <u><span id="blank">ssssssssssssssssss</span></u> <span id="arg2"> 	US</span></p>
	
	<form action='/mturk/tutorial2' role="form" method="post">
	  <div class="form-group">	
			
			<div class="btn-toolbar-vertical" data-toggle="buttons">

					<label class="btn btn-default btn-lg btn-block" id="checkboxes">
						<input type="checkbox" name="response[r1]" value="lived in" /><span id="option"><em>lived in</em></span>
					</label>
					<label class="btn btn-default btn-lg btn-block" id="checkboxes">
						<input type="checkbox" name="response[r2]" value="has nationality" /><span id="option"><em>has nationality</em></span>
					</label>
					<label class="btn btn-default btn-lg btn-block" id="checkboxes">
						<input type="checkbox" name="response[r3]" value="died in" /><span id="option"><em>died in</em></span>
					</label>
					<label class="btn btn-default btn-lg btn-block" id="checkboxes">
						<input type="checkbox" name="response[r4]" value="was born in" /><span id="option"><em>was born in</em></span>
					</label>

			</div>

			<div class="btn-toolbar-vertical">
				<!-- <button type="button" class="btn btn-danger btn-lg">Skip</button> -->
				<button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg btn-block" name="option" value="submit">Submit</button>	
				<button type="submit" class="btn btn-danger btn-lg btn-block" name="option" value="none">None of these</button>		
			</div>
			
			<input type="hidden" name="worker_id" value= "<%= @worker_id %>">
		</div>
	</form>
</div>

<!-- Modal -->
<div class="modal fade" id="myModal" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="myModalLabel" aria-hidden="true">
  <div class="modal-dialog">
    <div class="modal-content">
      <div class="modal-header">
        <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal"><span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span><span class="sr-only">Close</span></button>
        <h4 class="modal-title" id="myModalLabel">Example 1 Solution</h4>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-body">
				<ul class="list-group">
				  <li class="list-group-item">"Bill Clinton <span class="orange">has nationality</span> US" is correct, because the sentence indicates that he was the president of the US, and therefore he should be a US national.</li>
				  <li class="list-group-item">"Bill Clinton <span class="orange"> lived in</span> US" is correct, because a president lives in the country that he or she is president of.</li>
					<li class="list-group-item">"Bill Clinton <span class="orange"> born in</span> US" is <strong>NOT</strong> correct, even though it is factually true, because the sentence does not convey that.</li>
				</ul>
      			
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>